      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions representative of COU loading envelope; multiple loading rates or configurations evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717-specified loading configuration (5° offset compression-bending, 5 mm/min crosshead speed). Only one test condition evaluated; loading rate sensitivity and angular offset variation not explored. This factor falls below the required Gradation 2 level. Accepted under risk-informed rationale: model risk level 3 and medium decision consequence; ensemble agreement across three independent FEA implementations partially compensates for single-condition limitation."
